                        "description": "<p>The data was firstly normalized by the company (General metabolomics, Boston, USA, <a href='https://generalmetabolics.com' rel='noopener noreferrer' target='_blank'>https://generalmetabolics.com</a>).</p><p><br></p><p>Principal Component Analysis (PCA) was done with log10-transformed values. Sample values &gt;4 standard deviations from the mean value of PC1 and PC2 were considered as outliers.</p><p><br></p><p>The metabolite features were annotated by the company (General metabolomics, Boston, USA). Ions were annotated to the ionic derivatives of the metabolites listed in the <strong>KEGG </strong>database for&nbsp;<strong>Homo sapiens</strong>&nbsp;allowing 0.001 atomic mass units tolerance.</p>",
